High Voltage (AC/DC) played before and as the band walked on stage for the first set. All Is Known was introduced as a new song and contained alternate lyrics. During Billabong Valley, the guitar strap fell off the Flying Microtonal Banana while Ambrose was using it, with Joey jokingly telling Stu afterwards that his guitar was broken and that Ambrose should "stick to the blues harp". NOBODY'S BABY (Sheer Mag) played before and as the band walked on stage for the second set. Before Gamma Knife, the crowd started chanting for Stu to do a "shoey", to which he told them to "be reasonable" and that he was "too old for that". The Balrog was introduced as a new song. Am I In Heaven? contained a medley of teases and quotes including Alter Me, Cellophane, Rattlesnake, Hot Water, Head On/Pill and The River as well as a Sea of Trees jam with lyrics. This performance was filmed in 360-degree video and released as "King Gizzard & The Lizard Wizard - 360° Full Concert" on the Banalarama YouTube channel, featuring audio mixed by Stu

Stu later mentioned that they were recording the show that night, and that the unreleased song (Rock N’ Roll) was "kinda new". data.showtitle: Return of the Curse of Timeland
data.shownotes: This show was billed as Return of the Curse of Timeland (a rescheduling of their cancelled 2021 New Year's Eve Timeland Festival) and featured the debuts of Magenta Mountain, The Garden Goblin, The Dripping Tap, and Soy-Protein Munt Machine. Timeland was played over the PA as the pre-show music. A model of London’s Big Ben clock tower, approximately 20 ft (6 m) tall, with the words “Time is Ephemeral” and “Music is Ephemeral” written on the clock’s face was erected in the back right corner of the stage.  The clock hands ran forward at an accelerated pace throughout the show.  Am I in Heaven? contained Rattlesnake teases and Boogieman Sam quotes/teases. Evil Death Roll contained Robot Stop teases. Trapdoor was played for the first time known since 2016-09-09. (259 show gap) The Dripping Tap was introduced as a song about a tap that won’t stop dripping.  Smoke & Mirrors was played over the PA as the setbreak music. Hot Wax was played for the first time since 2018-06-20. (114 show gap) Gaia featured a drum solo by Cavs. Rattlesnake contained Boogieman Sam quotes and featured another Cavs drum solo, during which the band destroyed the clock tower presiding over the stage and passed out the pieces into the crowd. The on-stage carnage appears to have extended to some of the band’s equipment, as the final portion of Rattlesnake was performed with Joey playing the FMB and Stu singing with no instrument.

data.showtitle: Coachella Valley Music And Arts Festival
data.shownotes: This show was part of the 2022 Coachella Festival, held at the Empire Polo Grounds in Indio, CA.  The band played their set in spite of heavy winds and audio issues (including hearing Harry Styles in their in-ear monitors, which Joey stated was fine with him but not Stu), which may have prompted Joey’s exclamation at the start of the show.  Self-Immolate was introduced as a song about “lighting yourself on fire and running like a fucking nutbag.”  Gaia was introduced as a song about “all the funky weather going on”, then as a song about drones followed by a statement by Stu about how much he loves drones and technology in general, and featured a drum solo by Cavs.  Gamma Knife was introduced as a song about shanks.

For the show opening drum solo, it was discussed whether this should be added to the setlist as “Fury” in order to match with the show opening drum solo from the Melbourne ‘21 bootlegger release. It was decided that the drum solos labeled “Fury” by the band consist of a distinct double bass drum part which is absent from this drum solo and that other drum solos have been given different names (i.e. “Parking” on Chunky Shrapnel), therefore it was decided to leave this drum solo as a show note since we do not have definitive information on what it should be called. Based on these facts and the comments made by the band at this show, KGLW.net staff believe that the unavailable versions were also unfinished and that this is the first complete performance of Invisible Face. This was a three-hour marathon show and the first marathon show to be performed as a single set. The show opened with a video of Amby's father, Broderick Smith, introducing the band. Eyes Like the Sky through Evil Man was dedicated to Broderick Smith and featured Broderick’s narration from the Eyes Like the Sky album played over the PA while the band played, and photos of Broderick displayed on the large screen behind the band. Eyes Like the Sky, Year Of Our Lord, and The Raid were played for the first time since December 1, 2018 (192 show gap). Evil Man was played for the first time since February 18, 2016 (449 show gap). Prior to Gaia, Joey quoted “I Love L.A.” (Randy Newman). The Grim Reaper contained Torture Chamber quotes and “Intergalactic” (Beastie Boys) quotes. During the drum solo by Cavs following Astroturf the rest of the band left the stage, then returned and performed a metal vamp over the end of the solo. Shanghai featured the Grow Wings and Fly “let’s get real high” jam. Ambergris featured an extended intro during which Joey and Amby contemplated the nature of sexiness. The Dripping Tap was dedicated by Amby to Cavs’ dad and to his “first music teacher who said my voice sounds weird,” and contained Cellophane teases and Hot Water teases.

Joey shouted-out other performers at the festival: Yeah Yeah Yeahs, Sam Fender, Flume, Little Simz, and Marlon Williams. Joey acknowledged that the performance was taking place on stolen land, that the band will be voting yes in the upcoming Indigenous voice to Parliament referendum, and that the audience should do the same. KGLW.net Staff Notes: Special shout out to our very own @W.B.T.G. Slinger for the recording located on Archive.org and YouTube!

This show was cut short due to heavy winds at the festival site. The band (except Cavs) wore pilot uniforms for the full show. Prior to Gaia, Amby did a vocal tease of “Tequila” (The Champs). Gaia featured a drum solo by Cavs which led into a Motor Spirit jam. During Mars For The Rich a confetti cannon went off prompting Stu to sing "What the fuck is happening?" Am I In Heaven? contained Supreme Ascendancy quotes. The Grim Reaper contained "Intergalactic” (Beastie Boys) quotes and an appearance on stage by a dancing People-Vulture. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. Gaia through The Grim Reaper have been confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed via the written setlist for the show and contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

The Grim Reaper contained Torture Chamber and "Intergalactic” (Beastie Boys) quotes. Evil Death Roll contained Converge teases. Rattlesnake contained Boogieman Sam quotes and Flamethrower teases. K.G.L.W. (Outro) was on the printed setlist after Rattlesnake but was not played. Poster by Drew Millward

This show featured the first full performance of Motor Spirit. Rattlesnake was introduced as a song about snakes and contained Honey and Doom City teases. Honey contained a Sleep Drifter jam. Open Water featured a drum solo by Cavs. Ice V contained Hog Calling Contest teases. Cut Throat Boogie contained Sad Pilot teases and Rats In The Sky, Raw Feel, Field of Vision and Daily Blues quotes. Most Of What I Like contained a “Praise You” (Fatboy Slim) jam with Flight b741 teases. Following Most Of What I Like, Stu teased “Sweet Home Alabama” (Lynyrd Skynyrd). The Lord of Lightning was introduced as a song about shots by Stu, and about when Stu got struck by lightning by Ambrose, and contained Cut Throat Boogie and I'm In Your Mind teases. The Alter Me I Jam contained a Hypertension jam with lyrics and Witchcraft and Cellophane teases. I'm Not In Your Mind contained Robot Stop teases. Cellophane was also introduced as a song about shots by Stu and contained Motor Spirit quotes. Joey shouted out opener Grace Cummings after I'm In Your Mind Fuzz. Dragon was introduced as a song about dragons. Poster by Amy Jean; Edition of 100

This show featured the debut of Daily Blues. Grace Cummings unfortunately missed a third show due to illness, and was replaced with Naarm synth-punk band Dr Sure's Unusual Practice. Crumbling Castle contained a Witchcraft tease. The Fourth Colour contained a Daily Blues jam with lyrics. Rattlesnake contained an intro jam while Ambrose ran offstage. The jam contained Sleep Drifter, Honey, and Straws In The Wind teases and the song itself contained teases of Honey, “Whole Lotta Rosie” (AC/DC) and Sleep Drifter. Wah Wah contained a The River intro. Only Part I, II, and III of The River were performed and they contained a Sad Pilot tease and Wah Wah teases and quotes. The Bitter Boogie was played with the drum pattern from Muddy Water. Poster by Amy Jean; Edition of 150

Grace Cummings unfortunately missed a fifth show due to illness, and was replaced with Australian rock band C.O.F.F.I.N., who were joined by Ambrose during their opening set. The Lord of Lightning contained Cellophane and Witchcraft teases. I'm Not In Your Mind contained Am I In Heaven? teases and Daily Blues teases and quotes. The Bitter Boogie contained the drums from Muddy Water, Head On/Pill teases, Rats In The Sky, Hog Calling Contest, Antarctica, and Daily Blues quotes. Cellophane contained Rattlesnake teases. Ben Portnoy (drummer of C.O.F.F.I.N) joined the band for Rattlesnake, which contained Automation, Honey, Billabong Valley, and Minimum Brain Size teases, Honey teases and quotes with the lyrics changed to "Mad Dog tastes like honey", Daily Blues, Boogieman Sam, Oddlife, and Straws In The Wind quotes, and an Oddlife and Billabong Valley jam with lyrics. Poster by Amy Jean; Edition of 150

This show featured the debut of Field of Vision. Daily Blues was preceeded by a Rock and Roll (Led Zeppelin) tease. Gamma Knife contained a Motor Spirit tease. Boogieman Sam contained The Bitter Boogie and Work This Time teases, a Hog Calling Contest vocal jam, and Rats In The Sky quotes. I'm Not In Your Mind contained You Can Be Your Silhouette and Crumbling Castle teases. Cellophane contained Altered Beast teases. Before This Thing, which was introduced as a song about Ambrose and had alternate "New York City" lyrics, Converge was teased. After This Thing, Joey and Stu shouted out "Raygun", the Australian Olypmic breakdancer. Self-Immolate was introduced as a song about God. Straws In The Wind was dedicated to Alex Harvey.  Doom City contained an intro jam. Nuclear Fusion was not on the the printed setlist and featured an audience member (Gabby) on vocals. Rattlesnake contained Honey, Nuclear Fusion, and Oddlife teases, a Field of Vision quote, and Sleep Drifter teases and quotes.

Poster by Jason Galea
Standard Edition of 600
Holographic Edition of 150

Before Theia, Ambrose quoted Fried. The song itself contained Motor Spirit quotes, a The River jam with Wah Wah quotes, and Motor Spirit and The Silver Cord jams with lyrics. Joey did Michael Jackson-style vocal improv in the intro to Ambergris, which was introduced as a song about sperm whales and contained a short drum solo. Joey did an impression of Guy Fieri before Rats In The Sky. Cavs teased Rock and Roll (Led Zeppelin) before Sad Pilot. After Rats in the Sky, the band heckled Jason Galea to join on tambourine. Before Flight b741, the band got Cavs to hit the gong on his kit. After Flight b741, the band explained that Geelong, aka G-troit, is the sister city to Detroit, as both had a Ford production factory, which closed and destroyed the town. Joey teased Purple Haze (Jimi Hendrix) and Cavs teased Rock and Roll again. You Can Be Your Silhouette contained an extended intro where the band talked about how their talkback mics work and jazz notes. During the song itself, which contained a The End (The Doors) quote, it was described as a song about being yourself. During the intro to Straws In The Wind, the band joked about Ambrose swimming over to Canada and Ambrose walked up to the lights and sound booth.  Nuclear Fusion featured Vincent, a kid from the audience on the intro. Following the intro, Joey teased Twist (Korn). After Nuclear Fusion, Stu shouted out the stream crew. Honey contained O.N.E teases. Minimum Brain Size was introduced as a song about "loser hypermasculine people."  Prior to Rattlesnake Joey conducted a Q&A session with crowd members and Sam. Prior to Billabong Valley, Cavs ran offstage. During Billabong Valley, Joey said he can do a Limp Bizkit beat cause he doesn’t have an electric guitar and doesn’t want to take it to the [Dave] Matthews Bridge, followed by Ambrose climbing on top of the equipment truck on the side of the venue, leading to the line “I’m on the truck!” Her and I (Slow Jam 2), which was last played 2023-06-18 (50 show gap), contained a Slow Jam 1 intro as well as Iron Lung teases.

Poster by Jason Galea
Standard Edition - 600
Foil Edition- 200

Venusian 1 was last played 2023-03-11 (87 show gap). Witchcraft was swapped for Flamethrower because Stu had forgotten they played it the night before. Rattlesnake contained O.N.E., Automation, Minimum Brain Size, Sleep Drifter, Oddlife, and Honey teases, Am I In Heaven? vocal teases by Ambrose, and Boogieman Sam quotes. The intro to Gondii contained Shanghai quotes with some lyrics changed to “Bye Bye Chang’e” and the song itself contained Shanghai teases. Magma contained a Rats In The Sky intro. Sea of Trees contained a The Land Before Timeland tease, a You Can Be Your Sillouhette jam, and Daily Blues teases. Gamma Knife contained Motor Spirit teases and quote.

Poster by Amy Jean

Rattlesnake contained Automation and Sleep Drifter teases, Boogieman Sam quotes and Nuclear Fusion teases. O.N.E. and Sleep Drifter featured Stu on microtonal acoustic guitar. Open Water contained a Chang’e tease. The Lord of Lightning contained an Ice V tease. The Balrog contained a Cellophane tease. Before Hog Calling Contest, Joey mentioned that the band saw Dom Dolla at The Gorge the night before. Joe then asked the crowd to pretend to call hogs, and then invited sound manager Joe Santarpia to do the same. Stu then picked up an Intrasport shirt from a fan and told them they weren't playing it at the show, but would next tour, followed be an Intrasport tease. Flight b741 contained a false start due to Amby playing in the wrong key. Ice V contained a Head On/Pill tease and a Down Under (Men At Work) tease on drums. Dirt through Let Me Mend The Past featured Joey on acoustic guitar. Dirt conained a “Taylor” (Jack Johnson) tease. Mirage City was introduced as Paradise City (Guns N' Roses) followed by a Welcome to the Jungle quote from Amby. During Let Me Mend The Past, Ambrose crowdsurfed on an inflatable boat. Following Le Risque, Joey shouted out Jackson Devereux and Allen Dobbins (the stream film crew). Gondii contained a Dragon quote. The Silver Cord contained Extinction quotes. Daily Blues was quoted before Venusian 1, which was stopped halfway through due to the barricade being broken. During the stop, Joey called his mom and Stu and Joey sung part of Vegemite acapella, which was "performed" for the first time since 2016-05-14. Gaia, which was incomplete, featured a drum solo with a Motor Spirit tease. The Great Chain of Being was incomplete. Gaia Outro was on the printed setlist after Motor Spirit, but was cut. Poster by Jason Galea Normal - 2500 Foil - 500

Evil Death Roll contained Iron Lung teases and quotes.  Sad Pilot contained Hot Water teases.  Rats In the Sky was dedicated to Elvis Presley.  In Daily Blues, Ambrose quotes I Feel Like a Woman (Shania Twain) while wearing cowboy hats from her Vegas residency. Shanghai contained vocal samples from a slot machine, Magenta Mountain teases, and Grow Wings and Fly... quotes. The Grim Reaper also contained samples from a slot machine, chants of "cashing the check" and "Vegas", as well as Money Maker (Ludacris), Viva Las Vegas (Elvis Presley), and Intergalactic (Beastie Boys) quotes. Perihelion was introduced as a new song called Break Stuff (Limp Bizkit), then Ambrose quoted the song. Dragon contained The Great Chain Of Being teases.  Billabong Valley was teased prior to Rattlesnake, which contained Nuclear Fusion and Sleep Drifter teases.

Rattlesnake contained Nuclear Fusion, O.N.E. and Automation teases and Honey teases & quotes. Ice V contained Mirage City teases. Hog Calling Contest featured Joey on acoustic guitar. Following Set Amby quoted She'll Be Coming 'Round the Mountain (traditional).  Magenta Mountain contained The Grim Reaper quotes.

The Dripping Tap was unfinished. Rattlesnake contained Nuclear Fusion and Sleep Drifter teases. After Rattlesnake, Ambrose quoted an old Australian ad. Flamethrower featured a drum solo by Cavs. Extinction and Set featured the debut of the upgraded synth table (Nathan). Set contained Extinction quotes and Temporary Secretary (Paul McCartney) and The River teases. The River contained Thunderstruck (AC/DC) and Sad Pilot teases.

The Wheel was last played on 2024-05-29 (61 shows). Most Of What I Like was last played on 2024-05-31 (59 show gap). God Is Calling Me Back Home contained Green River (Creedence Clearwater Revival) and Le Risque teases. Le Risque was performed without the typical break between Cavs' and Ambrose's verses. Hog Calling Contest featured sound tech Joe Santarpia, whose birthday it was, doing pig noises. Most Of What I Like contained a Praise You (Fatboy Slim) jam. The Wheel contained Magma teases in the intro. Plastic Boogie contained a Happy Birthday To You tease. Following the song, the band thanked the crowd, everyone who followed them on tour, opening band King Stingray (who were invited onto stage), the crew, and Jason Galea. Hot Wax was introduced as a song by Jason Galea. Venusian 2 contained Hot Wax teases. Following Motor Spirit the band shouted out Allen and Jackson from the stream crew. Rattlesnake contained teases of Billabong Valley and Cellophane. At the end of the show, Ambrose quoted Nookie (Limp Bizkit).

data.shownotes: Slow Jam 1 featured Ambrose on saxophone and contained an Am I In Heaven? tease. Empty was performed for the first time since 2014-12-19 (644 show gap), and was performed with flute for the first time. Hot Wax was played by request of Wayne Gordon (who recorded I'm In Your Mind Fuzz and Quarters! at Daptone Studios and made a brief appearance on stage) and contained an Am I In Heaven? tease. A fan named Callum was brought onto stage to play Superbug on Stu's guitar instead of Stu. Magenta Mountain contained Forty Six & 2 (Tool) and Magma teases. The Grim Reaper contained Forty Six & 2 (Tool) teases and Intergalactic, Sabotage (both Beastie Boys), and Torture Chamber quotes. Following The Grim Reaper, Joey said he was ripping off Wes Borland (of Limp Bizkit), and Ambrose said he needed a red hat (Fred Durst's signature hat). Swan Song contained Magenta Mountain teases and quotes. Le Risque featured Jay Weinberg on drums instead of Cavs. Ice V featured Joey on flute during the intro and contained a quote of Aqualung (Jethro Tull) and teases of Ants & Bats and Blindness (The Fall). Raw Feel contained Am I In Heaven? teases. Hot Water contained I'm In Your Mind and Robot Stop teases.  Following Hot Water, Joey shouted out festival act The Mystery Lights, saying they were the first band they co-headlined with in America. Boogieman Sam contained The Bitter Boogie, Whole Lotta Rosie (AC/DC) and Riff Raff (AC/DC) teases. During Straws In The Wind, Ambrose walked through the crowd to Jason at the soundboard and when he returned to stage, he did an impression of Fred Durst. After Straws In The Wind, the band pretended it was Jason's birthday and sang Happy Birthday to him. During Pleura, Joey said "Fuck Donald Trump", with Ambrose responding "Juicy [Jason] for President!" Dimathaya Burarrwanga and Yimila Gurruwiwi from King Stingray joined the band for Rattlesnake on yiḏaki (didgeridoo), and Dimathaya quoted Treaty (Yothu Yindi). At the end of the show, Joey said Free Palestine and Ambrose led the crowd in a chant of "Free Free Palestine".

This show was played with The Orchestre Lamoureux conducted by Chad Kelly. After Eternal Return, Chad Kelly took a bathroom break, leading the band to do an impromptu jam. The Grow Wings and Fly jam had a Rattlesnake tease. This Thing was introduced as a song about Busy P.

data.shownotes: Before the band went on stage, they were introduced by Uncle Michael West. During Motor Spirit, Stu shouted out "I love heavy metal!". Following Work This Time Joey thanked Jimi Hendrix.  The tuneup for Le Risque contained a Hot Water tease.  Before Hot Water, Stu announced that "this song is not called Hog Calling Contest" and invited sound tech Joe Santarpia to do pig noises, which he declined. Hot Water contained Whole Lotta Rosie (AC/DC) teases.  Intrasport, which was played without the synth table, was dedicated to Darren Hayes from Savage Garden. Rattlesnake featured Dimathaya Burarrwanga and Ngalakan "Billy" Wanambi from King Stingray on yiḏaki (didgeridoo) and contained Ghost Spirits (Yothu Yindi) quotes by Dimathaya. Hog Calling Contest was on the written setlist after Le Risque but was not played due to issues with Stu's equipment.
